    mechanismPhysiology: "At alkaline pH 8.6, hemoglobins migrate toward the anode (+) at different rates based on net charge. Migration order (fastest to slowest, cathode to anode): C/A2/E → S → F → A. Mnemonic: 'Cats And Skunks Fight Always.' At acid pH 6.2, charge differences change, allowing separation of hemoglobins that comigrate at alkaline pH. HbC separates from HbA2/HbE. HbS separates from HbD/HbG.",
