    overview: "All blood cells arise from pluripotent hematopoietic stem cells (HSCs) in the bone marrow through a process called hematopoiesis. Understanding the maturation sequence of each cell lineage is fundamental to recognizing abnormal cells in leukemia, myelodysplasia, and other hematologic disorders.",
