    clinicalRelevance: "Erythroid: pronormoblast → basophilic normoblast → polychromatic normoblast → orthochromic normoblast → reticulocyte → mature RBC. Granulocytic: myeloblast → promyelocyte → myelocyte → metamyelocyte → band → segmented neutrophil (also eosinophil, basophil). The MYELOCYTE is the last stage capable of mitosis. Monocytic: monoblast → promonocyte → monocyte → tissue macrophage. Megakaryocytic: megakaryoblast → promegakaryocyte → megakaryocyte → platelets (cytoplasmic fragmentation). Lymphoid: lymphoblast → prolymphocyte → mature lymphocyte.",
